@NODE "recording" "recording"
@TOC "MAIN"


      Recording
      ---------

      MTRS has four recording routines: 

      * MODE 1 = recording 
      * MODE 2 = recording + playback (Full duplex) 
      * MODE 3 = recording + playback of two tracks (Full duplex) 
      * MODE 4 = recording + playback of three tracks (Full duplex) 

      MODE 1 needs the smallest and MODE 4 the highest computing-time.
      Importantly: Select the optimal mode before beginning of recording. 
      Thus will be achieved the highest possible sampling-frequency. Operate 
      more in the mode 1 and 2. 

      Assign the desired tracks to the recording and playback channels. 
      Click on the RECORD-TRACK1 in the main window until will be displayed 
      the desired track number. Repeat this process with PLAY1 to PLAY4 
      (dependent on the recording mode). The RECORD-button has the highest
      priority. Overlaps of the tracks will be avoided automatically by MTRS.

      The sampler-microphone will switch on and off with MIC. 

      If you want to record from the left channel then set CHAN on L - 
      otherwise CHAN on R. 

      Start the @{"sampler-monitor" LINK "monitor"} now. 

      Before the first recording must be input a name for the project in the
      main window.

      Click on REC in the main window. 

      If you'll execute an INTERRUPT-test, select "Yes" in the request window 
      - otherwise "No". If you'll abort the recording then press "Cancel".
      Other processes can disturb the recording process. The INTERRRUPT-test 
      monitors the recording. He needs however computing time. Switch it off 
      with slow processors. 

      MTRS waits now for the beginning of the recording. 
      Press the left mouse button. The recording begins. 

      The right mouse button will abort the recording.
@ENDNODE

