@NODE "system requirements" "system requirements"
@TOC "MAIN"


      Minimum requirement: 

      - AMIGA 500 
      - harddisk 
      - 8-bit-soundsampler for centronics interface 
      - 1 MByte RAM 
      - Kickstart 2.0 
      - AHI V4

      One recommends: 

      - at least ECS Amiga
      - high speed harddisk 
      - at least 68020-Prozessor 
      - more memory 
      - Kickstart 3.1
@ENDNODE

@NODE "tips&tricks" "tips & tricks"
@TOC "MAIN"

      Tips & tricks 
      ------------- 

      Work with more than eight tracks
      -------------------------------- 

      MTRS can show more than eight tracks with the PING-PONG effect. 
      Mix all tracks with that 8 channel mixer. Start disk-mix. A new 
      project will be created with two tracks. It contains all eight tracks.
      You can repeat this process. The quality decreases however. 
      Don't repeat the process any longer than three times. 

      Inserts from tracker modules
      ---------------------------- 

      The tracker module must present as 8 bits AIFF stereo or mono sample. 
      I operate with OKTAMED SOUNDSTUDIO. Select under menu adjustments 
      the menu option mixing routine. Select disk 8 bits. Start playback now. 
      Input a sample name. Select the format AIFF 8 bits. The module will be
      saved as AIFF sample. Start MTRS and open the Toolbox window.
      Click on IMPORT. Select your AIFF sample. Click on import. MTRS creates 
      a new project.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "toolbox window" "toolbox window"
@TOC "MAIN"

     Select in the menu window the menu option Toolbox. 

     Area FLAG: 

     The field SONG END shows the length of the longest track. 
     The field SONG TIME shows the play-time of the project. 
     It depends on the project length and the playback rate.
     Increase the reproducing frequency shorten the play time. 

     The fields MEM 1 to MEM 4 store positions of the project. 
     So you can fast regain important places. MEM 1 to MEM 4 operate 
     identically. Through click on the SET-button the current position 
     will be stored and displayed. If you click on MEM, the stored position 
     will taken over. 

     > CONVERT: 

     Here can be exported and imported tracks - partly or completely. 
     Input in the field START the initial position and in the field END 
     the final position. The sample length will be displayed in SAMPLE LEN. 
     Select the track number in the field SELECT. The length of the track will
     be displayed in the field TRACK LEN. 

     Press the EXPORT-button. Input a name for your sample. The sample will
     be stored as 8SVX file. 

     If you have processed the sample, you can click on the IMPORT-button.
     Select in the file request window your sample and press IMPORT.
     The sample will be inserted in the project. MTRS checks now
     whether the sample was entered in the INFO file. If it is correct, 
     the sample will be inserted at correct position. Otherwise MTRS asks you
     whether you'll insert the sample to current position (Toolbox window). 
     Importantly: The new sample data will repleace the area!  

     If sample is a AIFF sample then will create a new project.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "transport functions" "functions"
@TOC "MAIN"

      The transport control was had a feeling by a tape recorder.
      (functions STOP, START,PLAY,REW,FFW and REC) 

      STOP  - abort playback 
              (menu "transport/stop"; 
              combination of keys: left Amiga+E) 

      START - start playback from the position zero 

      PLAY  - start and continue playback at the 
              current position 

      REW   - move counter back 
              (corresponds to rewinding with the tape) 
            - with 8-channel-playback no function 

      FFW   - move counter fast forward 
              (corresponds to fast forward winding with the tape) 
            - with 8-channel-playback no function 

      REC   - start recording 
              (menu "transport/record")
@ENDNODE

@NODE "playback 2ch" "2 channel playback"
@TOC "MAIN"

      Playback 2 channel processor 
      ---------------------------- 

      Open your MTRS project. Select PLAY 2 in the main window. Click on 
      the START or PLAY button in the main window. The display turns green 
      and the multitasking will be switched off. Playback can be stopped with
      the right mouse button.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "playback 4ch" "4 channel playback"
@TOC "MAIN"


      Playback 4 channel DMA 
      ----------------------

      Open your MTRS project. Select PLAY 4 in the main window. Click on 
      the START or PLAY button in the main window. You can adjust the 
      track volume with the four volume sliders in the main window. 

      slider 1 - track 1, right channel 
      slider 2 - track 2, left  channel 
      slider 3 - track 3, left  channel 
      slider 4 - track 4, right channel 

      If you'll move fast forward in the project, press FFW button.
      With the REW-butten you can move to back in the project. Also, you can
      modify playback frequency. Click on FREQUENCE. Input your desired value.
      (see also menu Transport/ Frequency) 
      Important: DMA playback frequencies over 29 kHz are possible only with 
      ECS or AGA Amigas on activation of a VGA mode. The highest frequency 
      is 50 kHz.
      You can abort playback with the STOP button. 
      If you'll switch off the multitasking, select HQ ON. 
      You can abort the playback with the left mouse button.   
@ENDNODE

@NODE "playback 8ch" "8 channel playback"
@TOC "MAIN"


     Playback 8 channel DMA 
     ---------------------- 

     Open your MTRS project. Select PLAY 8 in the main window. Click on the 
     START or PLAY button in the main window. FFW and REW don't have 
     a function with the 8 channel playback. You can modify the playblack 
     frequency in the field FREQUENCE. Importantly: DMA playback frequencies
     over 29 kHz are possible only with ECS or AGA Amigas on activation of a 
     VGA mode. The highest frequency is 50 kHz. You can abort playback
     with STOP button. 

     Open 8 track stereo mixer window in the menu window. You can adjust the 
     the position for each track with the eight panorama sliders. You can adjust
     the track volume with the eight volume sliders. 
     The MASTER volume sliders determine the final volume. 
     MIXVOL% determine the mixing ratio. 
     You can switch on and off the stereo playback with the STEREO button. 
     It can occur distortions with mono playback. Then degrade the MIXVOL% value. 
     If the TEST button is switched on, MTRS will be checked processor and disk 
     rate. If playback frequency is too high, playback will be aborted. 
     The FREQ/2 button halve the playback frequency (for playback frequencies 
     more highly 28 kHz in the PAL display mode). 

     You can disable the multitasking. Select HQ ON.
     If you'll stop the playback then press the left mouse button. 

     The 8 channel playback need much arithmetic-performance. 
     A 68020-processor will be recommended.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "PlayAHI" "PlayAHI"
@TOC "MAIN"


     Playback 8 channel AHI 
     ---------------------- 

     Open your MTRS project. Select PLAY AHI in the main window. If AHI is not
     initialized, a window opens, in which you'll the number of channels 
     entered. If you press "Cancel", AHI will removed. Otherwise, you can
     select the AHI mode and the mix frequency in the next window.
     MTRS checks the selected mode.
     Click on the START or PLAY button in the main window. You can modify 
     the playblack frequency in the field FREQUENCE. 
     Importantly: DMA playback frequencies over 29 kHz are possible only 
     with ECS or AGA Amigas on activation of a VGA mode. The highest 
     frequency is 50 kHz. You can abort playback with STOP button. 

     Open 8 track  mixer AHI +DSP window in the menu window. 
     The window can be opened only with initialized AHI mode.
     You can adjust the the position for each track with the eight 
     panorama sliders. You can adjust the track volume with the eight 
     volume sliders. 
     The MASTER volume sliders determine the final volume. 
     BOOST determine the mixing ratio.
     
     Note:
     
     Not all modes supports all functions. If you select another display 
     mode, AHI will again initialized.
     
     Read please the AHI guidance, in order to use all possibilities!
      
@ENDNODE


